<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Dreamachine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="http://juniperhills.net/weekly.html" class="external text" title="http://juniperhills.net/weekly.html" rel="nofollow">Dream Weaver</a></i> Don Bolles, LA Weekly, July 26 - August 1, 1996</li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.headpress.com/ShowProduct.aspx?ID=40" class="external text" title="http://www.headpress.com/ShowProduct.aspx?ID=40" rel="nofollow">Headpress 25: Burroughs And The Dreamachine</a></i> Edited by David Kerekes (2003) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1900486261" class="internal">ISBN 1-900486-26-1</a></li>
<li><i><a href="http://softskull.com/detailedbook.php?isbn=1-932360-01-8" class="external text" title="http://softskull.com/detailedbook.php?isbn=1-932360-01-8" rel="nofollow">The Chapel of Extreme Experience: A Short History of Stroboscopic Light and the Dream Machine</a></i>[sic] by John Geiger (2003) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1932360018" class="internal">ISBN 1-932360-01-8</a></li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.researchpubs.com/Blog/?page_id=13&amp;product_id=54" class="external text" title="http://www.researchpubs.com/Blog/?page_id=13&amp;product_id=54" rel="nofollow">Re-Search: William S. Burroughs, Brion Gysin, Throbbing Gristle by V. Vale (Editor)</a> (1982) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0940642050" class="internal">ISBN 0-940642-05-0</a></i></li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.permuted.org.uk/dmplan.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.permuted.org.uk/dmplan.htm" rel="nofollow">Dreamachine Plans</a></i> by Brion Gysin (1994) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1871744504" class="internal">ISBN 1-871744-50-4</a></li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.danpetley.co.uk/dream%20machine/dreammachine.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.danpetley.co.uk/dream%20machine/dreammachine.htm" rel="nofollow">A detailed explanation of how to build a dream machine</a></i> By Dan Petley (2009)</li>
</ul>
